# ВОЗНЯ website — environment variables
#
# Copy to .env.local for local development:
#   cp .env.example .env.local
#
# In production (Vercel) set DATABASE_URL in Project Settings → Environment Variables.
# For Cursor Cloud Agents, add it under Cloud Agents → Secrets.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PostgreSQL connection string to the voznya-bot database.
#
# Powers the live community dashboard (/live) and the homepage live stats.
# The bot stores its URL as an asyncpg DSN (postgresql+asyncpg://...); this app
# also accepts that form and strips the "+asyncpg" driver suffix automatically.
#
# The database must be reachable from where the site runs (Vercel) — i.e. a
# public host/port, NOT the docker-compose internal host "db". Add sslmode=require
# for managed providers (Neon, Supabase, RDS, etc.).
#
# Examples:
#   DATABASE_URL=postgresql://voznya:password@db.example.com:5432/voznya?sslmode=require
#   DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://voznya:password@1.2.3.4:5432/voznya
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://voznya:password@host:5432/voznya?sslmode=require

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Telegram Login
#
# The bot is the single source of truth for users; the site only verifies that
# a login genuinely comes from Telegram for this bot and issues a session.
#
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN  — same token the bot uses (from @BotFather). Used server
#                       side to verify the Login Widget HMAC. Keep it secret.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TELEGRAM_BOT_USERNAME — the bot's @username WITHOUT the @. Public:
#                       it's embedded in the Login Widget on the client.
# AUTH_SECRET         — random string (>= 32 chars) used to sign session JWTs.
#                       Generate with: openssl rand -base64 48
# AUTH_COOKIE_NAME    — optional, defaults to "voznya_session".
#
# IMPORTANT: in @BotFather run /setdomain and point it to this site's domain,
# otherwise the Login Widget will refuse to render.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456:your-bot-token
NEXT_PUBLIC_TELEGRAM_BOT_USERNAME=your_bot_username
AUTH_SECRET=replace-with-a-long-random-string


